Set 1- Starting With CSS


Create a web page with an inline style that sets the background color of the page to blue.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS</title>
</head>
  <body style="background-color: #1515df;">
  <h1>Inline CSS Blue Background Page</h1>
   </body>
</html>

Create a web page with a heading and paragraph with information about CSS. Using internal CSS set the text color of the page to red and the background color of the paragraph to yellow.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">


  <title>CSS Information Page</title>
  <style>
    body { color: #ff0000; }


        p {background-color: #ffff00; }
  </style>


</head>
<body>
 
<h1>CSS: Cascading Style Sheets</h1>
<p>CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets.
  CSS is the language used to style on HTML file and tell the browser how it should render the elements on the page</p>


 
  </body>
</html>


Create a web page with 5 a tag similar to a navigation bar. Each link should change to a different color when it is hovered over.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">


  <title>Hover Effects</title>
  <style>
    a {display: inline-block; background-color: #cef0e5;
      font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
      padding: 5px;color: #000000;}


    a:hover {color: #bbff00;}


    .link1:hover {color: #00ff22;}


    .link2:hover {color: #07f3cc;}


    .link3:hover {color: #5c0303;}


    .link4:hover {color: #1506a0;}
   </style>


</head>
<body>
 
<h1>CSS: Hover Effects</h1>


<a class="link1" href="#">Courses</a>
<a class="link2" href="#">PW Skills Lab</a>
<a class="link3" href="#">Job Portal</a>
<a class="link4" href="#">Experiance Portal</a>
<a class="link5" href="#">Hall of fame</a>




  </body>
</html>


Create a web page with a list of tech stacks involved in full-stack web development where the even numbered items have a different background color than the odd-numbered items.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS:Background Color</title>
  <style>
   
    li:nth-child(even) {background-color: #aba5ce;padding: 5px;}


    li:nth-child(odd) {background-color: #a77c7c; padding: 5px;}
  </style>


</head>
<body>
  <h1>Tech Stacks involved in Full-stack Web Development</h1>
  <ul>
    <li>HTML and Semantics</li>
    <li>Starting with CSS</li>
    <li>Mobile responsive web pages</li>
    <li>Version Control and Git</li>
    <li>Getting Started with JavaScript</li>
    <li>Working with DOM</li>
    <li>Understanding Fundamental of Computer Science</li>
    <li>Getting Started with Database</li>
    <li>Starting with NodeJS and Express</li>
    <li>Understanding React and its Fundamentals</li>
    <li>Under Standing Hooks and Routers</li>


  </ul>




</body>
</html>


Create a web page with an image that is hidden until it is hovered over. Use a heading above the image that says hover below to reveal a surprise.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">


  <title>CSS:Hover Effect</title>
  <style>


.hidden-image {
    /* Opacity is the degree to which content behind an element is hidden opacity: 0; for hidden 1 for show opacity: 0.33; for partial show */


      opacity: 0;
      /* for display timing transition: opacity 0.5s ease; or transition: all 1s ease-out; */
     
      transition: all 1s ease-out; }


    .hidden-image:hover {opacity: 1;}
   
  </style>


</head>
<body>


  <h1>Hover below to reveal a surprise</h1>
  <img class="hidden-image" src="https://halloffame.pwskills.com/images/hall-of-fame-hero-img.svg" width="400 px" alt="Surprise Image">
 
</body>
</html>



Create a web page with a form where the input field has a yellow background color when it is focused on.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS:Form Effect</title>
  <style>
     input[type="text"]:focus {
      background-color: #ffff00;  
    }
  </style>


</head>
<body>


  <h1>Hover in Form to view yellow color</h1>
 
  <form>
    <label for="name">User Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" placeholder="Enter your name">
    <br><br>
    <label for="email">User Email:</label>
    <input type="text" id="email" name="email" placeholder="Enter your email">
    <br><br>
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
  </form>


</body>
</html>

