</body>
</html>




Set 2- More on CSS


Create a navigation bar similar to the below-mentioned image. The navigation bar must contain 5 navigation links that are properly placed within the navigation bar using the CSS box model. The navigation items must change their text color on hover.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS:navigation bar </title>
<style>




  nav ul {
  background-color: #4cbfce;
  display: flex;
  list-style-type: none;
  margin-right: 600px;
}
nav ul li {
    padding: 10px;
    text-align: left;
    flex:1px;
}
nav ul li a {
    color: #ffffff;
    transition: color 0.5s ease;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #ffffff;
}
nav ul li a:hover {
  color: #052406;
}
</style>


</head>
<body>
  <h1> 5-Navigation with hover effect </h1>
  <nav>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">About Us</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Blog</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Login</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</body>
</html>



Create a div centered with an image and paragraph similar to the image mentioned below.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS:div center effect </title>
<style>


.center-div {
  background-color: #7fffd4;
  margin-right: 380px; margin-left: 380px;
  padding: 25px;
  border-radius: 50px;
  align-items: center;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}


.center-div img {
   height: 300px;
   border-radius: 5%;
}




.center-div p {
  font-family:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif ;
  font-size: 20px; color: #000000;
}




</style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1> div centered with an image and paragraph </h1>




  <div class="center-div">
    <img src="https://learn.pwskills.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.pwskills.com%2Fassets%2Fuploads%2Fthumbnails%2F64215310af09d6aa495682f5.jpg&w=1920&q=75" alt="Sigma 2.0">
    <p> <b>Course Name :</b> PW Skills Sigma 2.0</p>
</div>




</body>
</html>



Create a navigation bar similar to question 1. For each navigation item use a different border style. 
         
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS:Nav with Border Style</title>
<style>
 
body{background-color: #f8b8d8;}


nav ul {padding: 0;margin: 0;}


nav ul li {display: inline-block;margin: 20px}


nav ul li a {padding: 15px;}


nav ul li:nth-child(1) a {border: 3px outset #d0e611;}
nav ul li:nth-child(2) a {border: 3px solid  #85797b;}
nav ul li:nth-child(3) a {border: 3px dotted #0000ff;}
nav ul li:nth-child(4) a {border: 3px double #800026;}
nav ul li:nth-child(5) a {border: 3px groove #00ff22;}




</style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1> Navigation Item use a different border style </h1>
  <nav>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">About Us</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Blog</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Login</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>




</body>
</html>




